cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.CY 

This paper proposes a data-intensive approach for inferring sentence-internal temporal relations, which is relevant for practical NLP applications. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the arXiv sub-category of Computational Linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also discusses the use of probabilistic models and machine learning techniques, indicating that it may also fit into the sub-categories of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Machine Learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper involves the analysis of linguistic features and the assessment of performance against gold standard corpora, suggesting that it could be relevant to the sub-categories of Information Retrieval (cs.IR) and Cybernetics (cs.CY).
